es\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Frederick_Reines#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>A graduate of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Stevens_Institute_of_Technology\" title=\"Stevens Institute of Technology\">Stevens Institute of Technology<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/New_York_University\" title=\"New York University\">New York University<\/a>, Reines joined the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Manhattan_Project\" title=\"Manhattan Project\">Manhattan Project<\/a>'s <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Los_Alamos_Laboratory\" title=\"Los Alamos Laboratory\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Los Alamos Laboratory<\/a> in 1944, working in the Theoretical Division in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Richard_Feynman\" title=\"Richard Feynman\">Richard Feynman<\/a>'s group. He became a group leader there in 1946. He participated in a number of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nuclear_tests\" title=\"Nuclear tests\" class=\"mw-redirect\">nuclear tests<\/a>, culminating in his becoming the director of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Operation_Greenhouse\" title=\"Operation Greenhouse\">Operation Greenhouse<\/a> test series in the Pacific in 1951.<\/p><p>In the early 1950s, working in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Hanford_Site\" title=\"Hanford Site\">Hanford<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Savannah_River_Site\" title=\"Savannah River Site\">Savannah River Sites<\/a>, Reines and Cowan developed the equipment and procedures with which they first detected the supposedly undetectable neutrinos in June 1956. Reines dedicated the major part of his career to the study of the neutrino's properties and interactions, which work would influence study of the neutrino for many researchers to come. This included the detection of neutrinos created in the atmosphere by <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cosmic_ray\" title=\"Cosmic ray\">cosmic rays<\/a>, and the 1987 detection of neutrinos emitted from <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/SN_1987A\" title=\"SN 1987A\">Supernova SN1987A<\/a>, which inaugurated the field of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Neutrino_astronomy\" title=\"Neutrino astronomy\">neutrino astronomy<\/a>.<\/p>","name":"Frederick Reines","place_of_birth":"Paterson, New Jersey","place_of_death":null,"text":"Frederick Reines , Physics, 1995","year":1995.0}